    "for the stellar sources with different T span scales.",
    "Figure 8a is for the stellar sources with T span < 200 days (within a few months), and Figure 8b is for the stellar sources with T span > 200 days (approximately one year or several years).",
    "The two groups of stellar sources with shorter and longer T span scales have been described in Section 3.3.",
    "After the R EXT Hα > 3 × δR EXT Hα screening condition, the numbers of stellar sources in the two groups are 757 and 4,120, respectively, as shown in Figures 8a and 8b.",
    "Because the stellar sources with lower (log R median Hα < -4.85) and higher (log R median Hα > -4.85) activity intensity exhibit different behaviors of Hα variability as described in Section 5.1, we distinguish the two categories of stellar sources in the analysis, which are separated with a vertical dashed line (corresponds to log R median Hα = -4.85) in each panel of Figure 8."
